1
00:00:42,647 --> 00:00:46,067
SOLD OUT ON YOU

2
00:00:46,651 --> 00:00:48,361
Mr. Mechoori.

3
00:00:49,779 --> 00:00:51,030
What took you so long?

4
00:00:52,407 --> 00:00:53,867
I told you I'd be home late.

5
00:00:54,492 --> 00:00:56,286
Why were you sleeping here?

6
00:00:56,369 --> 00:00:57,370
Did you take your meds?

7
00:00:57,453 --> 00:00:58,663
You only took one pack, right?

8
00:00:58,746 --> 00:01:00,248
Did you have dinner…

9
00:01:20,059 --> 00:01:21,561
I missed you.

10
00:02:42,392 --> 00:02:43,893
CAUTION
MAY CAUSE DIZZINESS

11
00:03:21,097 --> 00:03:22,598
Mr. Mechoori.

12
00:03:25,435 --> 00:03:26,436
Yes?

13
00:03:28,771 --> 00:03:29,772
Did you sleep well?

14
00:03:29,856 --> 00:03:31,816
Yes, I did.

15
00:03:33,568 --> 00:03:36,529
You didn't look comfortable
sleeping on the sofa last night,

16
00:03:36,612 --> 00:03:38,197
so I moved you to your room.

17
00:03:40,158 --> 00:03:41,200
Right.

18
00:03:41,284 --> 00:03:42,952
-Thank you.
-Sure.

19
00:03:45,163 --> 00:03:46,831
You look a bit tired today.

20
00:03:46,914 --> 00:03:48,374
Should I go run by myself?

21
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:50,460
No, it's fine. You can warm up first.

22
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:54,756
I'll be out soon.

23
00:03:57,842 --> 00:03:59,093
Okay.

24
00:04:02,930 --> 00:04:05,391
Mr. Mechoori, could you slow…

25
00:04:08,186 --> 00:04:09,187
Wait.

26
00:04:10,313 --> 00:04:12,231
Hey, I said slow down a little.

27
00:04:12,315 --> 00:04:13,566
What are you doing?

28
00:04:16,611 --> 00:04:18,029
What?

29
00:04:18,613 --> 00:04:20,823
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE

30
00:04:21,699 --> 00:04:23,284
Hey, Changsik!

31
00:04:23,368 --> 00:04:26,788
Hey, how could you just run off
without Changsik?

32
00:04:26,871 --> 00:04:29,332
He was desperately looking for you.

33
00:04:29,415 --> 00:04:31,417
Right, Changsik?

34
00:04:31,501 --> 00:04:32,919
You missed him, didn't you?

35
00:04:33,002 --> 00:04:34,295
I missed you.

36
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,676
Aren't you going to stretch?

37
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:42,136
Well…

38
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:43,096
Come on, Changsik.

39
00:04:44,097 --> 00:04:45,515
I was just about to.

40
00:04:45,598 --> 00:04:46,808
Stay here.

41
00:04:46,891 --> 00:04:48,017
What's his deal?

42
00:04:49,769 --> 00:04:52,605
Mr. Mechoori, how about getting a TV?

43
00:04:52,688 --> 00:04:54,065
I'll buy it for you.

44
00:04:54,148 --> 00:04:56,275
There's nothing to do, so I'm just bored.

45
00:04:56,359 --> 00:04:59,362
I want to catch up
on some TV shows and movies.

46
00:04:59,445 --> 00:05:00,530
And I miss variety shows.

47
00:05:00,613 --> 00:05:01,614
I missed you.

48
00:05:12,834 --> 00:05:13,876
Are you all right?

49
00:05:18,714 --> 00:05:19,715
Gosh, it's so hot.

50
00:05:19,799 --> 00:05:22,552
It's hot even in the morning.

51
00:05:22,635 --> 00:05:25,763
I heard there's a place where the weather
is like spring all-year round.

52
00:05:25,847 --> 00:05:28,558
Where was it? Somewhere in Colombia…

53
00:05:29,642 --> 00:05:30,893
Bogotá!

54
00:05:33,479 --> 00:05:35,440
-Bogotá!
-I missed you.

55
00:05:39,694 --> 00:05:40,528
What are you doing?

56
00:05:44,574 --> 00:05:46,117
Let's continue.

57
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:53,583
I've always wanted to see the sunset
from a lookout in Bogotá.

58
00:05:53,666 --> 00:05:56,210
Why do you have
so many things you want to see?

59
00:05:56,294 --> 00:05:57,920
Finish your stretching and come home.

60
00:05:59,088 --> 00:06:00,298
Let's go, Changsik!

61
00:06:06,429 --> 00:06:07,597
Let's go!

62
00:06:25,489 --> 00:06:26,824
Are you making bean sprout soup?

63
00:06:28,326 --> 00:06:29,493
What's wrong?

64
00:06:29,577 --> 00:06:30,953
-About what?
-What is it?

65
00:06:31,037 --> 00:06:31,871
Bean sprouts.

66
00:06:32,455 --> 00:06:33,956
-What?
-What?

67
00:06:48,012 --> 00:06:50,556
Na Som-yi!
Are you taking money from Mechoori again?

68
00:06:55,686 --> 00:06:57,146
Hey, Jin-yi.

69
00:06:57,230 --> 00:06:58,272
What is it?

70
00:07:00,149 --> 00:07:01,150
Didn't Som-yi come here?

71
00:07:02,109 --> 00:07:03,236
No, she didn't.

72
00:07:07,531 --> 00:07:09,033
Hey, where are you?

73
00:07:09,116 --> 00:07:11,827
School, my foot. Your teacher called
and said you weren't there!

74
00:07:11,911 --> 00:07:14,330
Are you crawling your way there?
You better move it!

75
00:07:17,917 --> 00:07:19,418
She's just about there now.

76
00:07:20,753 --> 00:07:22,421
But what were you doing?

77
00:07:28,052 --> 00:07:30,638
We were going to have breakfast.

78
00:07:31,889 --> 00:07:33,224
I haven't had breakfast either.

79
00:07:33,808 --> 00:07:34,684
Can I join you?

80
00:07:42,483 --> 00:07:45,611
Chili peppers are a must
in bean sprout soup.

81
00:07:45,695 --> 00:07:47,655
Isn't it spicy?
You can't handle spicy food.

82
00:07:48,239 --> 00:07:50,866
-You can't eat spicy food?
-He doesn't like spicy food.

83
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:54,245
Thanks.

84
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:00,209
What was that with Som-yi earlier?

85
00:08:00,293 --> 00:08:01,961
She was late to school again.

86
00:08:02,044 --> 00:08:04,422
Her homeroom teacher
probably thinks I'm neglecting her.

87
00:08:04,505 --> 00:08:06,632
Should I have a talk with Som-yi?

88
00:08:06,716 --> 00:08:08,467
As if she'd listen to you.

89
00:08:09,010 --> 00:08:11,012
Still, she seemed interested
in school these days.

90
00:08:11,095 --> 00:08:13,180
She wondered what they'd do
for creative activities.

91
00:08:13,264 --> 00:08:15,224
It's because they don't study
during that period.

92
00:08:15,308 --> 00:08:17,393
I have no idea
what's going to become of her.

93
00:08:17,476 --> 00:08:19,687
I think she's good with her hands.

94
00:08:20,521 --> 00:08:23,441
Last time, she won
the 3D-pen crafting contest.

95
00:08:24,442 --> 00:08:27,153
Did you forget
how she kept begging you for a 3D pen

96
00:08:27,236 --> 00:08:29,447
but quit two days after buying it for her?

97
00:08:36,912 --> 00:08:38,164
Don't eat so fast.

98
00:09:04,273 --> 00:09:06,400
You think you can just run away
and hide in here?

99
00:09:06,484 --> 00:09:09,820
Come out and see for yourself
what you've done!

100
00:09:09,904 --> 00:09:12,907
I'll make sure it's in your face
every moment of every day.

101
00:09:13,574 --> 00:09:15,117
Come out.

102
00:09:15,201 --> 00:09:17,328
Come out here!

103
00:09:17,411 --> 00:09:20,456
Come out here right now!

104
00:09:27,463 --> 00:09:28,589
What are you doing?

105
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:32,968
I'm just trying to digest. What?

106
00:09:46,649 --> 00:09:48,693
Yes, of course. Yes, Ms. Michelle.

107
00:09:48,776 --> 00:09:51,612
I'm on my way to pick him up.

108
00:09:52,196 --> 00:09:53,406
It's a 4:00 p.m. flight.

109
00:09:53,489 --> 00:09:54,782
Yes, ma'am. Goodbye.

110
00:10:08,379 --> 00:10:11,632
You've done a great job
of managing such a busy schedule.

111
00:10:12,508 --> 00:10:13,718
We've only just begun.

112
00:10:14,510 --> 00:10:18,431
I'll become much busier if we're to launch
other L'Étoile product lines.

113
00:10:18,514 --> 00:10:19,557
In Korea?

114
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:20,933
Yes.

115
00:10:21,767 --> 00:10:23,894
Your flight's in two hours, Mr. Seo.

116
00:10:24,437 --> 00:10:26,105
I'm not going to France.

117
00:10:26,188 --> 00:10:27,857
I threw away that ticket a long time ago.

118
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:30,943
Then, what about this suitcase?

119
00:10:31,026 --> 00:10:33,487
The vinyl records
that Michelle sent me are in there.

120
00:10:33,571 --> 00:10:36,240
I probably won't have time
to listen to them in Korea now,

121
00:10:36,323 --> 00:10:37,408
so send them back.

122
00:10:38,451 --> 00:10:40,494
Where are you going?

123
00:10:41,078 --> 00:10:41,912
HIT.

124
00:10:42,955 --> 00:10:46,417
Sir, Ms. Michelle
is not going to let this slide.

125
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:49,879
You could risk your position
by recklessly pushing ahead with this.

126
00:10:49,962 --> 00:10:50,880
I know.

127
00:10:50,963 --> 00:10:53,841
That's why I'm going alone.

128
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:06,270
We're currently working on the schedule
for La Fin Essence's follow-up broadcast.

129
00:11:07,062 --> 00:11:10,441
We've also requested QA tests
from domestic and international labs,

130
00:11:10,524 --> 00:11:12,651
and we're waiting for the results.

131
00:11:14,195 --> 00:11:16,739
Would you be able to proceed
with this right away?

132
00:11:20,493 --> 00:11:22,244
L'ÉTOILE LUMIÈRE EYE CREAM
PRODUCT INTRO

133
00:11:26,123 --> 00:11:29,335
I'm sure there are conditions
attached to this kind of proposal.

134
00:11:29,418 --> 00:11:30,294
What are they?

135
00:11:30,377 --> 00:11:32,755
Reinstate Ms. Dam Ye-jin.

136
00:11:32,838 --> 00:11:34,006
That's the only condition.

137
00:11:34,089 --> 00:11:37,051
Aren't you aware
of Dam Ye-jin's situation at the moment?

138
00:11:37,134 --> 00:11:39,470
That's why I'm telling you this.

139
00:11:39,553 --> 00:11:42,806
L'Étoile will not work with HIT
unless it's with Ms. Dam.

140
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:47,811
Where young souls breathed their last

141
00:11:47,895 --> 00:11:49,939
Jeon Jung-muk, I can't hear you!

142
00:11:50,022 --> 00:11:52,566
The wounded old pine trees…

143
00:11:54,860 --> 00:11:58,155
-Mechoori!
-Mechoori!

144
00:11:58,239 --> 00:11:59,907
-Mechoori!
-Let's go out!

145
00:11:59,990 --> 00:12:01,408
-Mechoori!
-Mechoori!

146
00:12:01,492 --> 00:12:02,826
-Mechoori!
-Mechoori, come on out!

147
00:12:02,910 --> 00:12:05,955
-Mechoori!
-Come on out!

148
00:12:06,038 --> 00:12:07,873
-Come on out!
-Let's go running together!

149
00:12:07,957 --> 00:12:10,584
-Come on out!
-Let's go! Gosh.

150
00:12:10,668 --> 00:12:12,211
-Come on!
-Let's go!

151
00:12:12,294 --> 00:12:13,462
Two, three!

152
00:12:13,546 --> 00:12:15,297
To the snow-covered front lines…

153
00:12:15,381 --> 00:12:16,924
Shouldn't you join them?

154
00:12:17,716 --> 00:12:20,761
Let's skip our morning exercise today.
We have to be somewhere.

155
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:24,598
What is it?

156
00:12:24,682 --> 00:12:26,600
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE
COMMUNITY FESTIVAL

157
00:12:27,476 --> 00:12:28,852
Hey, Mechoori.

158
00:12:28,936 --> 00:12:31,981
So you're not going to be
joining us this time either?

159
00:12:32,064 --> 00:12:33,065
No.

160
00:12:33,148 --> 00:12:36,193
After helping us prepare for the festival,

161
00:12:36,277 --> 00:12:38,153
won't it upset you

162
00:12:38,237 --> 00:12:39,697
-if you don't take part?
-Yeah.

163
00:12:39,780 --> 00:12:40,906
Nope.

164
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:44,410
Come on, man.

165
00:12:44,493 --> 00:12:46,412
Can't you just help us out tomorrow?

166
00:12:46,495 --> 00:12:48,706
Let's beat Deokpung Village 2 for once!

167
00:12:48,789 --> 00:12:50,874
Having me there won't change the results.

168
00:12:50,958 --> 00:12:52,835
We don't know that for sure.

169
00:12:52,918 --> 00:12:57,256
Mechoori, if you appear
as our village mascot

170
00:12:57,339 --> 00:13:01,260
and rattle them from the start,
we might actually win.

171
00:13:01,343 --> 00:13:03,220
I can't leave my farm unattended.

172
00:13:03,887 --> 00:13:05,848
Well, what did you expect him to say?

173
00:13:05,931 --> 00:13:07,975
Mechoori, I'll throw myself off from here.

174
00:13:08,058 --> 00:13:10,311
-I'm going to fall!
-Okay.

175
00:13:13,981 --> 00:13:15,024
This is scary.

176
00:13:18,027 --> 00:13:23,324
LET'S LIVE TOGETHER IN HARMONY

177
00:13:34,251 --> 00:13:36,795
If you tie it like that,
the wind will loosen it in no time.

178
00:13:39,006 --> 00:13:40,007
Right.

179
00:13:42,009 --> 00:13:43,677
Are you coming to the festival tomorrow?

180
00:13:44,345 --> 00:13:46,597
Yes. I have nothing else to do anyway.

181
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:48,349
I'm unemployed right now.

182
00:13:51,435 --> 00:13:53,187
How long will you be unemployed for?

183
00:13:54,938 --> 00:13:55,773
Sorry?

184
00:13:55,856 --> 00:13:59,652
I don't know what happened between you two
for Mechoori to act this way,

185
00:13:59,735 --> 00:14:03,572
but everything he's doing for you
is only because he feels responsible.

186
00:14:05,157 --> 00:14:06,158
What does that…

187
00:14:06,241 --> 00:14:08,827
He's managing the farm
and the raw material company.

188
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:16,627
He always has this strong sense
of responsibility.

189
00:14:17,461 --> 00:14:19,213
So don't lean on him so much.

190
00:14:32,309 --> 00:14:33,560
Responsibility?

191
00:14:34,728 --> 00:14:35,771
All right.

192
00:14:35,854 --> 00:14:37,690
Hey, what's that?

193
00:14:39,149 --> 00:14:41,276
-Look at that car.
-Who's that?

194
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:43,404
It looks so fancy.

195
00:14:59,253 --> 00:15:01,088
Hey, Mr. Lee.

196
00:15:09,013 --> 00:15:09,847
Mr. Park.

197
00:15:10,556 --> 00:15:11,557
Hello!

198
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:13,183
How are the preparations going?

199
00:15:13,267 --> 00:15:17,021
Yes! Well, thanks to you,
everything's going great.

200
00:15:17,104 --> 00:15:21,275
I've prepared
a brand new karaoke machine for you.

201
00:15:21,358 --> 00:15:22,776
Make some noise!

202
00:15:22,860 --> 00:15:24,653
Yeah!

203
00:15:25,529 --> 00:15:27,740
-What?
-Yeah!

204
00:15:32,036 --> 00:15:33,579
-I have a strong voice.
-Be careful.

205
00:15:33,662 --> 00:15:35,164
You shouldn't just…

206
00:15:42,046 --> 00:15:44,089
Hey, isn't that Dam Ye-jin?

207
00:15:44,173 --> 00:15:46,592
What is she doing here? What's going on?

208
00:15:46,675 --> 00:15:47,551
I'll tell you later.

209
00:15:49,303 --> 00:15:51,096
You'd better.

210
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:55,601
-Mr. Park.
-Yes?

211
00:15:55,684 --> 00:15:59,271
Is there a coffee shop nearby
that uses high-quality beans?

212
00:15:59,855 --> 00:16:02,858
Everyone's been working so hard.
I'll go get some drinks for them.

213
00:16:04,234 --> 00:16:05,152
There aren't any.

214
00:16:05,903 --> 00:16:07,946
-I'm sure I heard there was one.
-It's closed.

215
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:09,948
Right. It was Moon Cafe.

216
00:16:11,075 --> 00:16:12,785
It's probably closed right now.

217
00:16:12,868 --> 00:16:14,703
I'll go and see.

218
00:16:17,831 --> 00:16:18,916
Hey, Ae-ra.

219
00:16:23,295 --> 00:16:24,129
Moon Ae-ra!

220
00:16:25,839 --> 00:16:27,299
Is she out making a delivery?

221
00:16:27,382 --> 00:16:29,718
-She must be away at the moment.
-Well…

222
00:16:30,594 --> 00:16:32,304
Do you always talk like that?

223
00:16:33,472 --> 00:16:35,099
Wait here for a moment.

224
00:16:38,310 --> 00:16:39,228
Moon Ae-ra!

225
00:16:48,612 --> 00:16:50,239
Excuse me…

226
00:17:14,304 --> 00:17:17,516
Where did she go with the shop open?

227
00:17:28,777 --> 00:17:30,279
Moon Ae-ra!

228
00:17:31,905 --> 00:17:34,199
Geez, you scared me.

229
00:17:34,283 --> 00:17:35,576
What is it?

230
00:17:36,201 --> 00:17:37,035
What?

231
00:17:37,619 --> 00:17:39,663
Someone's here to order!
It's a group order!

232
00:17:42,082 --> 00:17:42,916
Excuse me.

233
00:17:44,543 --> 00:17:46,128
It's nice to see you again, Ms. Moon.

234
00:17:47,171 --> 00:17:49,631
I'd like ten cups of coffee
that the village elders like,

235
00:17:49,715 --> 00:17:51,675
and one cappuccino to go.

236
00:17:52,676 --> 00:17:54,553
Read the menu.

237
00:17:54,636 --> 00:17:56,138
I don't sell cappuccinos.

238
00:17:56,221 --> 00:17:57,639
I'm sorry.

239
00:17:57,723 --> 00:18:01,018
I smelled cinnamon in here,
so I thought it was on the menu.

240
00:18:03,061 --> 00:18:05,439
Where on earth is that scent coming from?

241
00:18:05,522 --> 00:18:06,940
Is he a dog or what?

242
00:18:10,152 --> 00:18:11,695
Those look like cappuccinos.

243
00:18:12,279 --> 00:18:14,281
I was just practicing.

244
00:18:14,364 --> 00:18:16,742
The foam's still too airy
for me to sell them.

245
00:18:16,825 --> 00:18:18,285
No, it's perfect.

246
00:18:20,287 --> 00:18:21,121
It looks nice.

247
00:18:21,205 --> 00:18:23,540
The milk foam still looks glossy
even though it's cooled.

248
00:18:23,624 --> 00:18:25,792
It must've been really tasty
when it was freshly made.

249
00:18:25,876 --> 00:18:26,919
Acting like you know…

250
00:18:27,002 --> 00:18:28,795
You get that soft sepia color

251
00:18:28,879 --> 00:18:31,381
only when silky foam
is layered over espresso

252
00:18:32,007 --> 00:18:33,300
with a golden crema.

253
00:18:33,383 --> 00:18:34,843
That's bound to be delicious.

254
00:18:35,427 --> 00:18:37,221
I'm getting curious about the taste.

255
00:18:37,888 --> 00:18:40,474
-Please excuse me.
-I don't sell coffee that's cooled.

256
00:18:45,229 --> 00:18:47,397
Wait just a moment then.

257
00:18:47,481 --> 00:18:50,359
You'll make a cappuccino for me?

258
00:18:50,442 --> 00:18:52,027
I charge double the price
for Seoulites.

259
00:18:53,111 --> 00:18:54,446
But if that's okay…

260
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:56,365
Double the price.

261
00:18:56,448 --> 00:18:58,200
Thank you very much.

262
00:19:38,407 --> 00:19:39,324
What?

263
00:19:40,617 --> 00:19:42,119
You two are living together?

264
00:19:42,995 --> 00:19:44,162
It just ended up that way.

265
00:19:44,246 --> 00:19:45,831
Hey, you said last time

266
00:19:45,914 --> 00:19:48,083
that you didn't have any feelings for her.

267
00:19:49,001 --> 00:19:49,960
It's not like that.

268
00:19:50,043 --> 00:19:53,005
Don't be silly. You of all people?

269
00:19:53,088 --> 00:19:55,090
Letting someone you don't like
live in your house?

270
00:19:55,882 --> 00:19:57,843
But I don't get Ms. Dam either.

271
00:19:57,926 --> 00:19:59,886
She canceled the show
after you told her to,

272
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:01,888
and even followed you here.

273
00:20:03,557 --> 00:20:04,725
No way…

274
00:20:05,517 --> 00:20:07,394
Does she still want the raw materials?

275
00:20:08,812 --> 00:20:10,522
I can't accept that.

276
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:14,651
Aren't you busy? Just go already.

277
00:20:16,153 --> 00:20:18,447
-Bye.
-Okay, bye.

278
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,074
That rascal…

279
00:20:27,289 --> 00:20:28,665
You're pretty late.

280
00:20:29,458 --> 00:20:30,292
I'm sorry.

281
00:20:31,084 --> 00:20:32,627
Did you and Jin-yi…

282
00:20:35,255 --> 00:20:37,674
Never mind. I made dinner. Sit down.

283
00:20:39,092 --> 00:20:40,135
Dinner?

284
00:20:59,654 --> 00:21:01,114
Don't eat it yet.

285
00:21:01,698 --> 00:21:02,699
Well…

286
00:21:03,492 --> 00:21:05,077
This is the highlight. Hang on.

287
00:21:10,374 --> 00:21:13,001
It's supposed to be a smiley face…

288
00:21:14,127 --> 00:21:17,047
I tried making this
since you can't eat any spicy food.

289
00:21:22,219 --> 00:21:25,680
-If it looks bad, I'll eat it.
-No, it smells good.

290
00:21:41,822 --> 00:21:43,448
Did you bite into a shell?

291
00:21:50,831 --> 00:21:52,374
Just spit it out.

292
00:21:55,001 --> 00:21:56,128
It tastes fine.

293
00:21:57,295 --> 00:21:58,755
I'm sorry.

294
00:21:58,839 --> 00:22:00,424
I'll just throw this away.

295
00:22:00,507 --> 00:22:01,925
It's okay.

296
00:22:05,178 --> 00:22:07,681
Mr. Mechoori, are you okay?

297
00:22:07,764 --> 00:22:09,558
Yes, I'm fine.

298
00:22:10,517 --> 00:22:12,894
You know, you're actually pretty clumsy.

299
00:22:12,978 --> 00:22:14,646
Why do you keep bumping into things?

300
00:22:14,729 --> 00:22:17,232
"Keep"? When did I ever
bump into things before?

301
00:22:17,315 --> 00:22:18,400
You bumped into the table

302
00:22:18,483 --> 00:22:20,694
and into the door last time.

303
00:22:20,777 --> 00:22:22,154
You hit it really hard.

304
00:22:36,334 --> 00:22:40,046
THE TRUTH BEHIND THE KISS

305
00:22:43,175 --> 00:22:44,551
He said he'd be really late…

306
00:22:46,178 --> 00:22:47,929
But he's seriously late.

307
00:22:57,647 --> 00:23:01,109
Turn off the lights before you sleep.
I'll come home as soon as I can.

308
00:23:21,087 --> 00:23:23,673
I NEED TO TELL YOU SOMETHING
I'LL STAY UP AND WAIT

309
00:23:25,508 --> 00:23:26,676
No.

310
00:23:27,761 --> 00:23:29,137
He'll be back soon anyway.

311
00:23:54,371 --> 00:23:55,956
When is he coming?

312
00:23:56,039 --> 00:23:58,124
"I'll come home as soon as I can."

313
00:23:58,208 --> 00:23:59,542
You said, "As soon as I can"!

314
00:24:29,239 --> 00:24:30,282
Did I wake you?

315
00:24:34,911 --> 00:24:36,288
Mr. Mechoori.

316
00:24:36,997 --> 00:24:38,415
What took you so long?

317
00:24:39,624 --> 00:24:41,459
I told you I'd be home late.

318
00:24:41,543 --> 00:24:43,253
Why were you sleeping here?

319
00:24:43,336 --> 00:24:44,462
Did you take your meds?

320
00:24:44,546 --> 00:24:46,840
You only took one pack, right?

321
00:24:46,923 --> 00:24:48,633
Did you have dinner…

322
00:25:45,398 --> 00:25:46,733
I'll head inside for a bit.

323
00:26:06,461 --> 00:26:10,006
Why did I do that? Why?

324
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,676
Why did I even say that?

325
00:26:20,433 --> 00:26:22,519
She's not picking up.

326
00:26:22,602 --> 00:26:24,270
Are you sure Ms. Dam is here?

327
00:26:24,354 --> 00:26:25,480
She said she's in Deokpung,

328
00:26:25,563 --> 00:26:27,774
but when I asked where,
she couldn't answer.

329
00:26:27,857 --> 00:26:29,234
Why?

330
00:26:29,317 --> 00:26:31,194
-Why do you think?
-I know!

331
00:26:31,277 --> 00:26:32,779
-Mr. Proper.
-I'm sure of it.

332
00:26:32,862 --> 00:26:35,573
-Of course. But Ms. Eom, did you hear?
-What?

333
00:26:35,657 --> 00:26:38,284
Mr. Seo said L'Étoile wouldn't do
the follow-up broadcast

334
00:26:38,952 --> 00:26:40,495
unless Ms. Dam does it.

335
00:26:41,329 --> 00:26:42,163
For real?

336
00:26:42,247 --> 00:26:44,582
That's why I'm rooting for Mr. Seo.

337
00:26:44,666 --> 00:26:46,292
And he buys us delicious snacks.

338
00:26:46,376 --> 00:26:47,210
Right. He does.

339
00:26:47,293 --> 00:26:48,294
The person you are…

340
00:26:48,378 --> 00:26:49,587
She's not picking up!

341
00:26:49,671 --> 00:26:51,256
Damn it.

342
00:26:51,339 --> 00:26:52,340
DEOKPUNG FESTIVAL

343
00:26:52,424 --> 00:26:53,591
DEOKPUNG ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

344
00:26:56,010 --> 00:26:57,262
DEOKPUNG COMMUNITY CENTER

345
00:26:57,345 --> 00:26:58,346
Could she be…

346
00:26:59,139 --> 00:27:00,557
This must be the place.

347
00:27:05,854 --> 00:27:08,940
Gosh, the weather's so nice.

348
00:27:09,023 --> 00:27:11,484
But why do you look so down?

349
00:27:11,568 --> 00:27:13,486
Did something happen last night?

350
00:27:14,362 --> 00:27:15,613
No.

351
00:27:15,697 --> 00:27:17,157
Of course not.

352
00:27:20,910 --> 00:27:22,036
Mechoori.

353
00:27:23,621 --> 00:27:24,456
I'm not joining.

354
00:27:25,874 --> 00:27:27,625
-Let's move our things.
-Okay.

355
00:27:29,752 --> 00:27:31,921
-Let's go.
-Right.

356
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:51,858
How have you been, Mr. Lee?

357
00:27:51,941 --> 00:27:53,443
What brings you here?

358
00:27:54,110 --> 00:27:56,821
I believe our two companies
are no longer involved with each other.

359
00:27:56,905 --> 00:27:58,865
I'm here to meet Ms. Dam.

360
00:27:58,948 --> 00:28:00,033
I heard she's staying here.

361
00:28:00,116 --> 00:28:01,618
Then, you'll know why she's here too.

362
00:28:01,701 --> 00:28:02,660
Don't worry.

363
00:28:02,744 --> 00:28:05,371
Ms. Dam will be back on air soon.

364
00:28:06,498 --> 00:28:08,750
La Fin Essence
isn't L'Étoile's only product.

365
00:28:11,920 --> 00:28:15,548
Do you really think
that would help Ms. Dam?

366
00:28:15,632 --> 00:28:17,759
It would be better than staying here.

367
00:28:22,305 --> 00:28:23,598
We have to use that to…

368
00:28:25,600 --> 00:28:27,060
Ms. Dam.

369
00:28:27,143 --> 00:28:28,144
Mr. Seo.

370
00:28:29,479 --> 00:28:31,231
What brings you here?

371
00:28:31,314 --> 00:28:33,191
I wanted to tell you something.

372
00:28:33,274 --> 00:28:34,526
Can you spare some time?

373
00:28:34,609 --> 00:28:36,152
What's this about?

374
00:28:36,236 --> 00:28:37,654
You can talk inside.

375
00:28:38,279 --> 00:28:40,240
Today's the day we settle this.

376
00:28:40,323 --> 00:28:42,283
We're having a community festival.

377
00:28:42,367 --> 00:28:44,118
Our village has lost ten years straight,

378
00:28:44,202 --> 00:28:46,496
so we're desperate for young competitors.

379
00:28:47,622 --> 00:28:50,500
I believe we need your help.
Could you please help us out?

380
00:28:52,544 --> 00:28:54,337
Would I be of any help though?

381
00:28:54,420 --> 00:28:56,089
Anyone under the age of 40 is an athlete.

382
00:29:02,053 --> 00:29:02,887
Then…

383
00:29:03,972 --> 00:29:05,014
Let's go.

384
00:29:05,723 --> 00:29:07,350
-Really? You're joining us?
-Sure.

385
00:29:07,433 --> 00:29:08,518
Let's go!

386
00:29:08,601 --> 00:29:10,478
-Let's talk after.
-Okay.

387
00:29:14,190 --> 00:29:15,942
What? Hey, Mechoori.

388
00:29:16,025 --> 00:29:17,235
Hurry up!

389
00:29:17,318 --> 00:29:18,486
MARKET STALLS THIS WAY

390
00:29:18,570 --> 00:29:19,571
Hey, Mechoori.

391
00:29:21,489 --> 00:29:23,950
Mechoori! You're really coming?

392
00:29:34,377 --> 00:29:36,254
Goodness, Dam Ye-jin.

393
00:29:37,589 --> 00:29:39,215
This is why she wasn't picking up.

394
00:29:41,384 --> 00:29:45,179
Are you Team Mr. Proper or Team Mr. Seo?

395
00:29:45,930 --> 00:29:46,931
Me?

396
00:29:48,558 --> 00:29:49,601
I'm Team Dam Ye-jin.

397
00:29:50,184 --> 00:29:51,269
Dam…

398
00:29:54,898 --> 00:29:56,524
Then, I'm Team Dam Ye-jin too!

399
00:29:57,066 --> 00:29:58,776
That was a great line.

400
00:29:59,485 --> 00:30:00,945
Have some coffee, everyone.

401
00:30:01,029 --> 00:30:02,030
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

402
00:30:02,113 --> 00:30:04,699
-Hey, can you taste this for me?
-Sure.

403
00:30:04,782 --> 00:30:07,827
Hey, bring some more kimchi
so we can have them cut.

404
00:30:07,911 --> 00:30:11,164
Sure thing! I'll go.

405
00:30:11,831 --> 00:30:12,665
Hey!

406
00:30:15,126 --> 00:30:17,921
Deokpung Village 1!

407
00:30:20,006 --> 00:30:21,674
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE 2

408
00:30:21,758 --> 00:30:23,468
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

409
00:30:32,435 --> 00:30:33,561
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

410
00:30:33,645 --> 00:30:35,104
DEOKPUNG FOOD STALL

411
00:30:35,188 --> 00:30:38,066
-Sweetie, come with us.
-Yes, ma'am.

412
00:30:38,149 --> 00:30:39,400
Let's go, Jong-il!

413
00:30:39,484 --> 00:30:41,736
-Let's go.
-Let's hurry!

414
00:30:50,912 --> 00:30:54,624
Thanks for coming, Ms. Okpo.
It must've been tough.

415
00:30:54,707 --> 00:30:56,417
It's fine.

416
00:30:56,501 --> 00:31:02,256
Making the trip to Deokpung Village 1
isn't difficult at all.

417
00:31:02,340 --> 00:31:06,970
I hear the winning village
gets a TV this year.

418
00:31:07,053 --> 00:31:09,180
Oh, dear! My goodness!

419
00:31:09,889 --> 00:31:12,976
Two years ago, we got a fridge.

420
00:31:13,059 --> 00:31:14,435
-With two doors!
-With two doors!

421
00:31:14,519 --> 00:31:16,646
And last year, we got a tractor.

422
00:31:16,729 --> 00:31:18,272
-Vroom!
-Vroom!

423
00:31:18,356 --> 00:31:20,775
If we win the TV as well this year,

424
00:31:21,359 --> 00:31:25,571
when will Deokpung Village 1
ever get their chance?

425
00:31:27,657 --> 00:31:29,158
It's fine!

426
00:31:29,242 --> 00:31:32,245
Even without those prizes,

427
00:31:32,328 --> 00:31:35,123
-we're doing quite fine.
-Since when?

428
00:31:35,206 --> 00:31:39,210
-Sparkle, sparkle.
-Sparkle, sparkle.

429
00:32:17,790 --> 00:32:20,793
This is practically cheating!

430
00:32:20,877 --> 00:32:22,795
Well, for your village,

431
00:32:22,879 --> 00:32:24,839
-you have Gi-bok, don't you?
-Right.

432
00:32:24,922 --> 00:32:26,257
Gi-bok is…

433
00:32:27,175 --> 00:32:30,011
-very healthy.
-Very healthy.

434
00:32:47,278 --> 00:32:48,613
-Get back in here.
-Yes, ma'am.

435
00:32:51,908 --> 00:32:53,785
Deokpung Village 2!

436
00:32:53,868 --> 00:32:55,828
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

437
00:32:55,912 --> 00:32:57,705
Deokpung Village 1!

438
00:32:57,789 --> 00:33:00,708
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

439
00:33:00,792 --> 00:33:02,960
Mic check. Can you hear me in the back?

440
00:33:03,044 --> 00:33:04,587
-Can you hear me?
-We can hear you!

441
00:33:04,670 --> 00:33:06,255
You can hear me? Okay, then.

442
00:33:06,339 --> 00:33:08,382
-Hello, everyone!
-Hello!

443
00:33:08,466 --> 00:33:14,347
I'm Deokpung Village 1's
lovable village chief, Jeon Won-taek!

444
00:33:15,431 --> 00:33:17,809
Nice to see you all!

445
00:33:17,892 --> 00:33:19,477
All right!

446
00:33:19,560 --> 00:33:21,354
The weather's great today, isn't it?

447
00:33:21,437 --> 00:33:22,313
-Yes!
-Yes!

448
00:33:22,396 --> 00:33:26,818
I'm thrilled that Deokpung Village 1

449
00:33:26,901 --> 00:33:30,238
and our dear neighbors,
Deokpung Village 2,

450
00:33:30,321 --> 00:33:35,535
are gathered here
on this great day to hold this festival.

451
00:33:36,994 --> 00:33:39,163
-You must be pretty close.
-Yes.

452
00:33:39,789 --> 00:33:45,419
Let's put aside
all our concerns and worries

453
00:33:45,503 --> 00:33:47,922
and just enjoy this day!

454
00:33:50,424 --> 00:33:52,135
-By all means…
-Geez.

455
00:33:52,218 --> 00:33:53,511
I hope today

456
00:33:54,178 --> 00:33:55,179
will continue to…

457
00:33:55,263 --> 00:33:57,557
Not only is he educated,
he's long-winded too…

458
00:33:58,141 --> 00:33:59,684
-Yeah!
-Yes.

459
00:33:59,767 --> 00:34:04,689
For 10, 20, 30 years to come,

460
00:34:04,772 --> 00:34:06,399
let us all combine our strength…

461
00:34:07,275 --> 00:34:08,609
Ta-da!

462
00:34:08,693 --> 00:34:09,944
All right. This time,

463
00:34:10,027 --> 00:34:14,866
we'll be deciding
who has the strongest arms in our village.

464
00:34:14,949 --> 00:34:17,577
Anyone who feels pretty strong
within their village

465
00:34:17,660 --> 00:34:19,579
can step up and answer the challenge.

466
00:34:19,662 --> 00:34:21,455
Come on out!

467
00:34:22,331 --> 00:34:23,332
Come on, let's go!

468
00:34:27,378 --> 00:34:29,380
Bow to greet each other.

469
00:34:30,173 --> 00:34:31,507
All right. Let's grab hands.

470
00:34:32,508 --> 00:34:34,302
Hold on tight.

471
00:34:36,137 --> 00:34:36,971
He's tough!

472
00:34:37,054 --> 00:34:39,473
Kwang-mo, I don't want to hurt your pride,

473
00:34:39,557 --> 00:34:41,559
so I'll wait five seconds before winning.

474
00:34:41,642 --> 00:34:43,227
Forget it. Just do your best.

475
00:34:43,311 --> 00:34:44,145
Don't be afraid.

476
00:34:44,228 --> 00:34:45,354
Hold on tight.

477
00:34:45,438 --> 00:34:46,981
Ready, set, go!

478
00:34:48,274 --> 00:34:49,192
You can do it!

479
00:34:50,401 --> 00:34:54,280
You can do it!

480
00:35:00,828 --> 00:35:01,662
More!

481
00:35:11,547 --> 00:35:14,258
Mr. Park, you can do it!

482
00:35:15,468 --> 00:35:19,180
Ms. Eom, I don't think I can do this…

483
00:35:20,056 --> 00:35:21,599
You can do it!

484
00:35:22,350 --> 00:35:24,810
I think I'm going to lose.

485
00:35:24,894 --> 00:35:26,562
I'm sorry.

486
00:35:42,620 --> 00:35:44,413
He's winning!

487
00:35:48,209 --> 00:35:49,418
Park Kwang-mo wins!

488
00:36:07,770 --> 00:36:09,313
Park Kwang-mo!

489
00:36:09,397 --> 00:36:11,732
-Park Kwang-mo!
-Park Kwang-mo!

490
00:36:12,316 --> 00:36:13,818
-Park Kwang-mo!
-Park Kwang-mo!

491
00:36:14,777 --> 00:36:15,778
Park Kwang-mo!

492
00:36:15,861 --> 00:36:17,280
VILLAGE 1 VS VILLAGE 2
1 : 0

493
00:36:17,363 --> 00:36:18,239
WOMEN'S ARM WRESTLING

494
00:36:18,322 --> 00:36:20,324
Gi-sun, let's go!

495
00:36:20,950 --> 00:36:22,285
Let's go!

496
00:36:24,704 --> 00:36:25,913
Kwang-mo,

497
00:36:25,997 --> 00:36:28,499
don't you know she's a reserve athlete
for the Asian Games?

498
00:36:28,582 --> 00:36:30,793
Her opponent's going to get crushed.

499
00:36:30,876 --> 00:36:32,586
No one from Deokpung Village 1?

500
00:36:33,796 --> 00:36:34,797
No one?

501
00:36:42,138 --> 00:36:43,597
Where are you going?

502
00:36:43,681 --> 00:36:45,349
Ms. Eom, you can't.

503
00:36:45,433 --> 00:36:47,518
She's a monster!
She's literally a reserve athlete.

504
00:36:49,562 --> 00:36:51,272
It's okay, Mr. Park.

505
00:36:51,939 --> 00:36:54,150
-No, don't!
-Don't…

506
00:36:54,233 --> 00:36:55,943
-Let's do this!
-You can't!

507
00:36:58,487 --> 00:37:00,865
Bow to greet each other!

508
00:37:00,948 --> 00:37:03,534
Okay, let's grab hands.

509
00:37:05,494 --> 00:37:07,330
-Go easy on her, Gi-sun.
-She can't win.

510
00:37:07,413 --> 00:37:09,123
-I can't watch.
-I can't look.

511
00:37:09,206 --> 00:37:13,419
Ready, set, go!

512
00:37:13,502 --> 00:37:16,172
-You can do it.
-You can do it.

513
00:37:26,474 --> 00:37:27,641
She's letting her stay on.

514
00:37:27,725 --> 00:37:29,435
-No way.
-She's going easy on her.

515
00:37:35,441 --> 00:37:37,777
No, wait. She actually has a chance.

516
00:37:45,910 --> 00:37:47,578
Deokpung Village 1 wins!

517
00:37:47,661 --> 00:37:48,996
I win!

518
00:37:55,961 --> 00:37:57,963
Yeah! I won!

519
00:38:01,175 --> 00:38:04,762
-We won!
-We won!

520
00:38:10,393 --> 00:38:12,269
Ae-ra, aren't I heavy?

521
00:38:12,353 --> 00:38:13,354
Shut your mouth.

522
00:38:15,981 --> 00:38:17,066
DISINFECTANT

523
00:38:20,069 --> 00:38:23,114
Ae-ra, I'm usually good at fighting--

524
00:38:23,197 --> 00:38:24,240
Shut your mouth.

525
00:38:30,037 --> 00:38:32,331
This really was the first time!
I've never done it before!

526
00:38:32,415 --> 00:38:34,500
Jong-yeon convinced me to try it
and I was curious.

527
00:38:34,583 --> 00:38:36,752
I promise not to smoke again.
Ae-ra, forgive me!

528
00:38:36,836 --> 00:38:39,713
Ae-ra, please let it slide just this once!

529
00:38:39,797 --> 00:38:41,048
Shut your mouth!

530
00:38:41,132 --> 00:38:43,968
You were smoking
because your stupid mouth is always open!

531
00:38:44,051 --> 00:38:46,220
I swear I won't.
Please forgive me just this once!

532
00:38:46,303 --> 00:38:47,721
-What's wrong with you?
-Please!

533
00:38:47,805 --> 00:38:52,601
It's because I'm worried about you!
What's gotten into you?

534
00:38:57,898 --> 00:38:58,732
Yeah!

535
00:39:01,610 --> 00:39:03,612
But this feeling's supposed to be
for Moon Ae-ra.

536
00:39:18,252 --> 00:39:19,795
Ae-ra…

537
00:39:36,103 --> 00:39:37,646
Why do I feel okay?

538
00:39:41,984 --> 00:39:43,152
I feel so calm.

539
00:39:45,196 --> 00:39:47,740
This next game is charades.

540
00:39:47,823 --> 00:39:48,949
Where were you from?

541
00:39:49,033 --> 00:39:50,201
-Okay, teams.
-I'm from Seoul.

542
00:39:50,284 --> 00:39:54,038
Please select your players now.

543
00:39:54,121 --> 00:39:55,456
Let's hurry and…

544
00:39:55,539 --> 00:39:56,707
Deokpung Village 1! What are…

545
00:39:56,790 --> 00:39:59,126
Come on, Deokpung Village 1! Focus!

546
00:39:59,210 --> 00:40:01,003
Hey, Jong-il! Stop eating rice puffs…

547
00:40:01,086 --> 00:40:03,214
All right, already. Give it a rest.

548
00:40:03,297 --> 00:40:06,175
Okay, who's going to do charades?

549
00:40:10,638 --> 00:40:12,139
Everyone's waiting.

550
00:40:12,890 --> 00:40:14,642
Stop eating, will you?

551
00:40:14,725 --> 00:40:16,101
Hurry up and come out.

552
00:40:18,687 --> 00:40:20,814
What's your name?

553
00:40:21,649 --> 00:40:23,317
Hello, ma'am. My name is Eric.

554
00:40:23,984 --> 00:40:24,818
"Eregi"?

555
00:40:26,612 --> 00:40:28,197
Yes, Eregi.

556
00:40:29,031 --> 00:40:29,907
Eregi.

557
00:40:30,866 --> 00:40:32,826
Eregi, come with me.

558
00:40:33,911 --> 00:40:35,287
What? Where are we going, ma'am?

559
00:40:38,165 --> 00:40:39,959
VILLAGE 1 VS VILLAGE 2
2 : 2

560
00:40:40,042 --> 00:40:41,919
CHARADES

561
00:40:43,087 --> 00:40:45,214
I don't know if that blonde
even knows Korean.

562
00:40:45,297 --> 00:40:47,967
Ready, set, go!

563
00:40:48,050 --> 00:40:49,677
TOO MANY COOKS SPOIL THE BROTH

564
00:40:55,391 --> 00:40:57,643
Eregi, just try anything.

565
00:40:57,726 --> 00:40:59,311
It's fine.

566
00:41:07,778 --> 00:41:10,197
Too many cooks spoil the broth!

567
00:41:10,281 --> 00:41:11,532
Correct!

568
00:41:15,869 --> 00:41:17,204
FALLING ON DEAF EARS

569
00:41:24,086 --> 00:41:26,922
-Falling on deaf ears!
-Correct!

570
00:41:27,006 --> 00:41:28,674
AS THE TWIG IS BENT, SO GROWS THE TREE

571
00:41:30,551 --> 00:41:31,802
As the twig is bent,

572
00:41:31,885 --> 00:41:34,597
-so grows the tree!
-Correct!

573
00:41:35,514 --> 00:41:37,266
He's crying.

574
00:41:37,349 --> 00:41:39,852
Crying over spilled milk!

575
00:41:39,935 --> 00:41:41,478
Correct!

576
00:41:42,896 --> 00:41:44,023
All right!

577
00:41:46,567 --> 00:41:47,568
What's that?

578
00:41:47,651 --> 00:41:50,321
EVERYONE LOOKS OUT FOR THEIR OWN SKIN,
BUT FEW RISK IT FOR OTHERS

579
00:41:53,449 --> 00:41:54,283
What is it?

580
00:41:55,284 --> 00:41:56,535
Just give it a try.

581
00:41:59,705 --> 00:42:02,708
Everyone looks out for their own skin,

582
00:42:02,791 --> 00:42:05,836
but few will risk it for someone else!

583
00:42:11,050 --> 00:42:14,887
Correct! Deokpung Village 1,
one minute and 35 seconds!

584
00:42:24,313 --> 00:42:25,898
Eregi, I can't believe this!

585
00:42:52,257 --> 00:42:54,176
Mechoori is our village genius.

586
00:42:54,259 --> 00:42:55,427
VILLAGE 1 VS VILLAGE 2
3 : 2

587
00:42:55,511 --> 00:42:57,262
-He's a genius.
-Of course.

588
00:42:57,346 --> 00:43:00,724
We're going to win this game for sure.

589
00:43:02,559 --> 00:43:04,311
Okay, get ready.

590
00:43:04,395 --> 00:43:06,063
-Get set.
-Let's go.

591
00:43:06,146 --> 00:43:07,314
Go!

592
00:43:07,398 --> 00:43:08,691
LET SLEEPING DOGS LIE

593
00:43:13,737 --> 00:43:15,364
Yeah, that's right!

594
00:43:17,449 --> 00:43:18,534
Sleep…

595
00:43:21,245 --> 00:43:22,621
And kiss?

596
00:43:22,705 --> 00:43:23,664
I missed you.

597
00:43:28,502 --> 00:43:31,672
Mechoori, why aren't you guessing?

598
00:43:33,006 --> 00:43:34,842
If you don't know, just skip it!

599
00:43:34,925 --> 00:43:36,593
-No, don't skip!
-It's okay.

600
00:43:36,677 --> 00:43:38,178
Pass!

601
00:43:40,556 --> 00:43:41,974
Pass!

602
00:43:42,057 --> 00:43:43,308
AT A LOSS FOR WORDS

603
00:43:46,895 --> 00:43:51,608
AT A LOSS FOR WORDS

604
00:43:51,692 --> 00:43:53,485
KISS

605
00:43:58,741 --> 00:43:59,616
Pass!

606
00:44:01,118 --> 00:44:03,120
All right, it's okay. No, it's not okay!

607
00:44:03,203 --> 00:44:04,580
Look, he's just getting started.

608
00:44:04,663 --> 00:44:05,956
Just watch.

609
00:44:06,874 --> 00:44:08,000
LIE THROUGH ONE'S TEETH

610
00:44:13,046 --> 00:44:15,132
Just say something!

611
00:44:17,092 --> 00:44:18,093
Pass!

612
00:44:18,177 --> 00:44:19,678
Mr. Mechoori!

613
00:44:20,721 --> 00:44:22,097
What are you doing?

614
00:44:22,723 --> 00:44:25,100
-This is so frustrating!
-Mechoori!

615
00:44:25,184 --> 00:44:26,560
We're going to lose!

616
00:44:29,104 --> 00:44:30,063
Your…

617
00:44:34,318 --> 00:44:35,152
Lips…

618
00:44:37,821 --> 00:44:38,655
Love…

619
00:44:53,003 --> 00:44:53,962
I love your lips!

620
00:44:54,046 --> 00:44:55,631
KIND WORDS BRING KIND RESPONSES

621
00:44:55,714 --> 00:44:59,551
I LOVE YOUR LIPS!

622
00:45:11,688 --> 00:45:13,065
Wrong!

623
00:45:13,941 --> 00:45:15,984
Deokpung Village 1, time's up!

624
00:45:17,528 --> 00:45:19,363
Hey, you fool!

625
00:45:31,333 --> 00:45:32,167
Mr. Mechoori…

626
00:45:33,168 --> 00:45:34,002
Goodness…

627
00:45:34,836 --> 00:45:36,213
I'm sorry.

628
00:45:36,922 --> 00:45:37,923
I'm really sorry!

629
00:45:41,093 --> 00:45:42,886
-So what was it?
-What?

630
00:45:42,970 --> 00:45:44,513
What was the lips thing?

631
00:45:45,055 --> 00:45:46,473
What about you and Mr. Park?

632
00:45:47,641 --> 00:45:48,934
What's going on with you two?

633
00:45:49,685 --> 00:45:51,562
Am I being left out again?

634
00:45:52,646 --> 00:45:54,815
SOM'S VARIETY SHOP

635
00:45:54,898 --> 00:45:58,610
I'm sure it'll take ages for you
to dry your hair

636
00:45:58,694 --> 00:46:01,071
with that weak dryer you have at home.

637
00:46:01,154 --> 00:46:03,448
Well, as for this hair dryer,

638
00:46:03,532 --> 00:46:06,159
it's completely different
from those weak ones.

639
00:46:06,243 --> 00:46:10,289
It's designed to be low-noise,
you don't have to worry about waking up

640
00:46:10,372 --> 00:46:11,456
your family at night.

641
00:46:11,540 --> 00:46:13,625
Won't it use a lot of electricity?

642
00:46:13,709 --> 00:46:15,794
There's no need to worry about that!

643
00:46:15,877 --> 00:46:17,629
It has the highest energy
efficiency rating,

644
00:46:17,713 --> 00:46:19,756
so using it 30 minutes a day
for a month will add

645
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:21,550
only a few thousand won more to your bill.

646
00:46:21,633 --> 00:46:24,011
But it's so small.
I bet the air flow's not that great.

647
00:46:24,094 --> 00:46:26,013
There's no need to explain.
Feel it yourself.

648
00:46:26,597 --> 00:46:28,265
Doesn't it feel so nice… Oh, gosh!

649
00:46:28,348 --> 00:46:29,600
-Hey!
-Sorry!

650
00:46:29,683 --> 00:46:32,102
-Geez…
-Goodness.

651
00:46:33,770 --> 00:46:35,480
Anyways, I don't need it.

652
00:46:35,564 --> 00:46:37,232
Come on, sir.

653
00:46:37,316 --> 00:46:39,484
If you apply warm air
to your scalp regularly,

654
00:46:39,568 --> 00:46:42,195
it'll boost blood flow
and keep your mind sharp.

655
00:46:42,279 --> 00:46:44,906
It's perfect for helping you
stay warm in winter.

656
00:46:44,990 --> 00:46:46,742
And you know you have to dry your toes

657
00:46:46,825 --> 00:46:49,661
after showering
to prevent athlete's foot, right?

658
00:46:49,745 --> 00:46:52,623
This can help you from head to toe.

659
00:46:52,706 --> 00:46:53,832
And you still don't need it?

660
00:46:55,584 --> 00:46:56,835
How much is it again?

661
00:46:56,918 --> 00:46:59,338
Only 49,000 won.

662
00:46:59,421 --> 00:47:01,632
-I want one too!
-Me too!

663
00:47:01,715 --> 00:47:02,591
Please line up.

664
00:47:02,674 --> 00:47:04,593
-Line up, please!
-Hey, get in line!

665
00:47:07,012 --> 00:47:08,805
I thought I was watching you, Ms. Dam.

666
00:47:08,889 --> 00:47:10,974
I know, right?
There was a mini Dam Ye-jin here.

667
00:47:15,520 --> 00:47:16,521
Hang on.

668
00:47:21,610 --> 00:47:22,944
Som-yi.

669
00:47:24,571 --> 00:47:26,073
Here, drink this.

670
00:47:30,160 --> 00:47:32,329
I'll cover you. Drink up.

671
00:47:46,385 --> 00:47:47,469
VILLAGE 1 VS VILLAGE 2
3 : 3

672
00:47:47,552 --> 00:47:48,762
Ta-da!

673
00:47:50,180 --> 00:47:53,350
Look at this, everyone.
It's three to three right now.

674
00:47:53,433 --> 00:47:57,771
Okay, it's time for the last game
to decide the winner.

675
00:47:57,854 --> 00:48:01,942
Let us begin the highlight
of the festival, the relay race.

676
00:48:02,025 --> 00:48:05,070
Deokpung Village 2!

677
00:48:18,750 --> 00:48:21,878
Let's go, Deokpung Village 2!

678
00:48:26,842 --> 00:48:27,676
Thank you.

679
00:48:34,224 --> 00:48:35,684
Don't push yourself too hard.

680
00:48:42,858 --> 00:48:44,568
Okay, runners.

681
00:48:44,651 --> 00:48:47,154
Please take your place
at the starting line.

682
00:48:47,237 --> 00:48:48,071
Good luck, Mr. Seo.

683
00:48:54,453 --> 00:48:55,746
-Jin-yi.
-Yeah?

684
00:48:55,829 --> 00:48:56,830
Let's change our order.

685
00:48:58,457 --> 00:48:59,499
Sure.

686
00:49:03,587 --> 00:49:07,299
Ready, set, go!

687
00:49:11,344 --> 00:49:12,888
You're doing great!

688
00:49:23,565 --> 00:49:24,399
Just a bit more!

689
00:49:24,483 --> 00:49:25,942
Let's go! Come on!

690
00:49:33,241 --> 00:49:34,367
There you go! A bit more!

691
00:49:43,418 --> 00:49:44,461
Mechoori!

692
00:49:48,757 --> 00:49:51,176
Matthew! Yes! Go!

693
00:49:52,219 --> 00:49:53,345
All the way!

694
00:49:55,889 --> 00:49:56,723
Mechoori!

695
00:50:25,335 --> 00:50:26,670
-Mechoori!
-No, no!

696
00:50:26,753 --> 00:50:28,463
-What is he doing?
-Pass the baton!

697
00:50:28,547 --> 00:50:29,881
Why is he still running?

698
00:50:29,965 --> 00:50:31,216
What…

699
00:50:31,299 --> 00:50:32,217
Hey!

700
00:50:41,142 --> 00:50:44,020
He should be disqualified!
He ran half a lap more!

701
00:50:44,104 --> 00:50:45,605
I mean, it can happen!

702
00:50:45,689 --> 00:50:47,357
It happens! It's fine!

703
00:50:47,440 --> 00:50:50,402
-No, it can't! He should be disqualified!
-It's not like that!

704
00:50:51,403 --> 00:50:53,113
Okay, all right!

705
00:50:53,196 --> 00:50:54,030
He's disqualified!

706
00:50:57,659 --> 00:50:58,827
Mr. Park!

707
00:51:00,161 --> 00:51:01,621
Mr. Park! Oh, no!

708
00:51:02,664 --> 00:51:03,915
Mr. Park!

709
00:51:21,558 --> 00:51:24,227
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE 2 HAS ALREADY WON

710
00:51:24,311 --> 00:51:26,938
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE 1

711
00:51:34,070 --> 00:51:35,447
Can I call you?

712
00:51:42,162 --> 00:51:43,163
Well…

713
00:51:46,333 --> 00:51:47,167
Okay.

714
00:51:58,011 --> 00:51:59,179
I have something to tell you.

715
00:52:00,263 --> 00:52:01,264
Do you have a minute?

716
00:52:04,768 --> 00:52:06,519
It's going to take a while to clean up.

717
00:52:06,603 --> 00:52:07,979
-How about tomorrow?
-No, tonight.

718
00:52:10,565 --> 00:52:11,566
It has to be tonight.

719
00:52:17,113 --> 00:52:18,949
All right. Let's go and talk.

720
00:52:26,331 --> 00:52:27,707
You're not cold?

721
00:52:27,791 --> 00:52:29,834
No, I'm okay.

722
00:52:33,630 --> 00:52:34,839
Geez!

723
00:52:34,923 --> 00:52:35,966
What the heck?

724
00:52:36,049 --> 00:52:37,425
Let me talk to you.

725
00:52:42,138 --> 00:52:43,181
You know,

726
00:52:43,682 --> 00:52:45,600
I came here
because I was worried about you.

727
00:52:45,684 --> 00:52:47,352
Geez, why would you worry about me?

728
00:52:50,063 --> 00:52:54,025
You know 70% of your body
is made up of work.

729
00:52:54,651 --> 00:52:57,404
But that condition for survival
just disappeared,

730
00:52:58,196 --> 00:53:00,031
so I didn't know if you'd make it or not.

731
00:53:00,907 --> 00:53:03,451
I brought all of these for you. See?

732
00:53:08,790 --> 00:53:09,958
Give them to me then.

733
00:53:11,835 --> 00:53:13,586
You didn't seem to need them.

734
00:53:17,716 --> 00:53:18,800
You look well, Ye-jin.

735
00:53:19,884 --> 00:53:21,136
You finally look human.

736
00:53:27,475 --> 00:53:28,476
Ms. Eom.

737
00:53:28,560 --> 00:53:31,062
Then, for the drive on the way back…

738
00:53:31,146 --> 00:53:32,605
-Thank you.
-I'll do it.

739
00:53:33,398 --> 00:53:34,816
We'll head back now, Ms. Dam.

740
00:53:34,899 --> 00:53:37,277
Okay. I'll be back after I get some rest.

741
00:53:38,737 --> 00:53:41,322
But don't rest for too long, okay?

742
00:53:41,406 --> 00:53:42,949
Without you, our team is like…

743
00:53:43,033 --> 00:53:45,577
-A hot dog without the sausage.
-That's it. Got that?

744
00:53:45,660 --> 00:53:47,328
-Go on, now.
-Bye.

745
00:53:47,412 --> 00:53:49,622
-Drive safely.
-We'll get going. Bye!

746
00:53:49,706 --> 00:53:52,083
-Make sure to eat well.
-Okay.

747
00:54:02,177 --> 00:54:04,179
It seems you're busy here as well.

748
00:54:07,515 --> 00:54:09,059
Could you spare some time for me now?

749
00:54:16,649 --> 00:54:18,693
I heard from Ms. Yang earlier

750
00:54:20,070 --> 00:54:22,614
that you collapsed the day you came here.

751
00:54:26,868 --> 00:54:27,869
I'm sorry.

752
00:54:29,162 --> 00:54:31,122
I wanted to apologize to you in person.

753
00:54:31,873 --> 00:54:33,333
Come on.

754
00:54:33,416 --> 00:54:35,001
What happened with HIT

755
00:54:35,085 --> 00:54:37,003
was just a result of my decision.

756
00:54:37,670 --> 00:54:40,006
It's nothing for you to apologize about.

757
00:54:40,090 --> 00:54:42,842
Still, if you hadn't become involved
with L'Étoile,

758
00:54:42,926 --> 00:54:44,928
you wouldn't be here right now.

759
00:54:48,807 --> 00:54:51,017
I wanted to come earlier,

760
00:54:51,810 --> 00:54:54,187
but I didn't want to apologize
with empty words,

761
00:54:54,270 --> 00:54:55,939
so it took a while.

762
00:54:58,149 --> 00:54:59,359
Ms. Dam,

763
00:55:01,694 --> 00:55:03,071
come back to Seoul with me.

764
00:55:08,743 --> 00:55:11,204
We're doing another QA test
for La Fin Essence

765
00:55:11,287 --> 00:55:12,914
and a follow-up broadcast afterwards.

766
00:55:13,623 --> 00:55:16,543
We're discussing launching
other L'Étoile products on HIT as well.

767
00:55:16,626 --> 00:55:18,753
-Mr. Seo, I--
-Ms. Dam.

768
00:55:19,420 --> 00:55:21,673
Allow me to help so you can go back

769
00:55:22,882 --> 00:55:24,300
to the work that you love to do.

770
00:55:25,301 --> 00:55:27,053
Come with me, Ms. Dam.

771
00:55:37,313 --> 00:55:41,901
DEOKPUNG RESTING SPOT

772
00:55:42,986 --> 00:55:45,071
Aren't you curious about what I'll say?

773
00:55:48,408 --> 00:55:50,785
I guess you already know
what I'm going to say.

774
00:55:51,995 --> 00:55:53,913
But I know everything too.

775
00:55:55,707 --> 00:55:58,209
I know you're already aware of my feelings

776
00:55:58,835 --> 00:56:00,753
and that you've been playing dumb.

777
00:56:02,088 --> 00:56:04,883
Still, I wanted to tell you this myself.

778
00:56:08,094 --> 00:56:11,514
Thanks to you, I got to live
in a warm neighborhood

779
00:56:12,557 --> 00:56:15,268
and learned how to share
care and affection with others.

780
00:56:15,351 --> 00:56:18,313
I feel like I've grown roots here now.

781
00:56:18,396 --> 00:56:19,230
So thank you.

782
00:56:22,233 --> 00:56:24,903
And along with that gratitude,

783
00:56:25,486 --> 00:56:26,946
I've grown to like you too.

784
00:56:28,448 --> 00:56:29,824
How do you feel about me?

785
00:56:36,456 --> 00:56:37,624
What are you doing?

786
00:56:38,291 --> 00:56:40,126
You're supposed to tell me to get a grip.

787
00:56:40,793 --> 00:56:42,086
Because I'm Som-yi's sister.

788
00:56:47,550 --> 00:56:48,593
Jin-yi.

789
00:56:49,260 --> 00:56:52,013
-I--
-Gosh, you're so frustrating.

790
00:56:55,016 --> 00:56:56,768
I'm sorry, Jin-yi.

791
00:56:57,352 --> 00:56:58,519
Did you know

792
00:56:59,562 --> 00:57:01,272
you were looking at Dam Ye-jin all day?

793
00:57:02,982 --> 00:57:05,193
Don't make excuses for your own feelings.

794
00:57:05,276 --> 00:57:07,654
You saw what just happened to me, right?

795
00:57:09,572 --> 00:57:10,615
Bye.

796
00:57:10,698 --> 00:57:13,284
I feel embarrassed,
so wait three minutes and leave.

797
00:57:27,966 --> 00:57:29,717
Thank you, Mr. Seo.

798
00:57:30,552 --> 00:57:31,386
But…

799
00:57:32,387 --> 00:57:34,514
You don't have to put in
so much effort to help me.

800
00:57:34,597 --> 00:57:37,892
I know you can return without my help.

801
00:57:38,518 --> 00:57:41,854
I just don't want you
to waste too much time here--

802
00:57:41,938 --> 00:57:43,565
Sung-mi said I looked well.

803
00:57:46,192 --> 00:57:48,027
I've never been told that before.

804
00:57:50,280 --> 00:57:51,573
These days,

805
00:57:52,365 --> 00:57:55,827
I feel like I'm walking a path
that I used to run through.

806
00:57:57,954 --> 00:58:00,623
I never realized how long an hour was

807
00:58:00,707 --> 00:58:03,042
even though I'd do live shows
for two hours every day.

808
00:58:04,502 --> 00:58:05,587
Are you sure you're okay?

809
00:58:06,629 --> 00:58:07,797
I really am okay.

810
00:58:09,507 --> 00:58:11,676
I think I need this time.

811
00:58:12,635 --> 00:58:15,346
So don't feel guilty about me.

812
00:58:16,097 --> 00:58:18,391
The one who should
actually apologize to me

813
00:58:18,474 --> 00:58:19,434
is myself.

814
00:58:21,644 --> 00:58:22,478
Still…

815
00:58:24,147 --> 00:58:27,483
feel free to tell me
whenever you need my help.

816
00:58:31,195 --> 00:58:32,030
I'm…

817
00:58:33,823 --> 00:58:36,034
waiting for you, Ms. Dam.

818
00:58:39,954 --> 00:58:41,539
I'm good at waiting

819
00:58:42,582 --> 00:58:44,083
even though I don't enjoy it.

820
00:59:53,820 --> 00:59:56,864
Korea really is far away.

821
01:00:00,702 --> 01:00:02,870
L'ETOILE
EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR SEO ERIC

822
01:00:11,838 --> 01:00:13,047
What are you doing out here?

823
01:00:14,674 --> 01:00:16,634
You must have talked for quite a while.

824
01:00:25,059 --> 01:00:26,561
PAIN RELIEF SPRAY

825
01:00:29,272 --> 01:00:31,232
Were you late because of this?

826
01:00:31,315 --> 01:00:33,693
Apply that before bed.
And go to the hospital tomorrow.

827
01:00:36,988 --> 01:00:38,239
Let's go inside.

828
01:00:41,367 --> 01:00:42,660
Sit down.

829
01:00:43,327 --> 01:00:44,871
We have a lot to talk about.

830
01:01:07,101 --> 01:01:08,561
My nickname is Fact Check.

831
01:01:08,644 --> 01:01:11,564
So let me check a few things.

832
01:01:12,607 --> 01:01:13,441
Okay.

833
01:01:14,150 --> 01:01:16,694
In that relay race earlier,

834
01:01:16,778 --> 01:01:17,695
why did you do that?

835
01:01:19,447 --> 01:01:21,032
You hurt your ankle yesterday.

836
01:01:27,789 --> 01:01:29,415
And those…

837
01:01:29,499 --> 01:01:30,458
Those corner guards.

838
01:01:30,541 --> 01:01:32,376
Why did you install them?

839
01:01:33,961 --> 01:01:34,962
It's in case

840
01:01:35,546 --> 01:01:36,672
you get hurt.

841
01:01:39,592 --> 01:01:41,177
Why did you make that daily schedule?

842
01:01:42,303 --> 01:01:43,596
Why did you say

843
01:01:43,679 --> 01:01:46,057
you'd give me one pack of pills a day?

844
01:01:46,140 --> 01:01:47,809
Why did you bring me here?

845
01:01:47,892 --> 01:01:50,478
Why are you so nice to me?

846
01:01:58,194 --> 01:02:00,071
Are these questions difficult to answer?

847
01:02:06,869 --> 01:02:07,870
That day…

848
01:02:08,830 --> 01:02:09,831
Why did you do it?

849
01:02:10,706 --> 01:02:13,084
What? What day?

850
01:02:15,795 --> 01:02:18,881
The day you kissed me.

851
01:02:27,890 --> 01:02:29,392
Is that question difficult to answer?

852
01:02:33,104 --> 01:02:34,146
No, I…

853
01:02:40,444 --> 01:02:43,698
I didn't take the medicine
that you left that day.

854
01:02:45,283 --> 01:02:47,702
I was waiting to talk to you
when you came back.

855
01:02:49,036 --> 01:02:50,955
But when I heard you coming,

856
01:02:51,038 --> 01:02:54,000
my heart started pounding,
and I pretended to be asleep.

857
01:02:55,293 --> 01:02:58,462
I was wondering when I should act
as if I'd just been woken up.

858
01:02:58,546 --> 01:03:02,466
But you kept doing stuff for me
so I could sleep well,

859
01:03:02,550 --> 01:03:04,844
so I couldn't open my eyes.

860
01:03:06,262 --> 01:03:09,724
My heart was pounding so loudly
that they were ringing in my ears.

861
01:03:09,807 --> 01:03:11,684
Do you know how worried I was

862
01:03:11,767 --> 01:03:13,603
that you'd hear it too?

863
01:03:21,569 --> 01:03:22,904
You were pretending to be asleep?

864
01:03:22,987 --> 01:03:23,988
Yes!

865
01:03:25,740 --> 01:03:28,451
I did it because I was nervous.

866
01:03:30,620 --> 01:03:33,122
-What?
-You still haven't answered my question.

867
01:03:34,415 --> 01:03:35,541
What was the question?

868
01:03:39,545 --> 01:03:41,339
Why did you pretend not to remember?

869
01:03:42,882 --> 01:03:44,383
I don't think that was the question.

870
01:03:46,594 --> 01:03:49,013
I pretended not to remember
because of you.

871
01:03:49,096 --> 01:03:52,350
You're the one who first acted
like nothing happened.

872
01:03:52,433 --> 01:03:53,309
And that's not all.

873
01:03:53,392 --> 01:03:55,394
You freaked out
even when our arms touched.

874
01:03:55,478 --> 01:03:57,188
You took Changsik and ran off without me.

875
01:03:57,772 --> 01:03:59,690
How could I say anything to you?

876
01:04:05,237 --> 01:04:06,405
What's that look?

877
01:04:06,489 --> 01:04:08,074
Do I look like a fool to you right now?

878
01:04:09,033 --> 01:04:10,826
I'm Dam Ye-jin!

879
01:04:10,910 --> 01:04:15,039
I'm not someone
who usually rambles on like this!

880
01:04:17,500 --> 01:04:19,585
This is all because of you, Mr. Mechoori.

881
01:04:22,880 --> 01:04:23,714
Then, this…

882
01:04:27,426 --> 01:04:28,928
is because of you, Ms. Dam.

883
01:05:54,680 --> 01:05:56,682
SOLD OUT ON YOU

884
01:06:29,799 --> 01:06:31,634
What did you two do last night?

885
01:06:32,676 --> 01:06:35,513
I think I first fell for you
when I saw you like this.

886
01:06:35,596 --> 01:06:37,098
You talk to yourself too loudly.

887
01:06:37,181 --> 01:06:38,432
I said that for you to hear.

888
01:06:38,516 --> 01:06:40,434
They can't get enough of each other!

889
01:06:40,518 --> 01:06:44,105
Mechoori! It's Som-yi!
What am I going to do?

890
01:06:44,188 --> 01:06:46,816
Why on earth
did you bring that woman here?

891
01:06:46,899 --> 01:06:50,069
What happened to Som-yi was my fault.

892
01:06:50,152 --> 01:06:52,196
I've put everything
on the line for Ms. Dam.

893
01:06:52,279 --> 01:06:54,156
But is this the best you can do for her?

894
01:06:54,240 --> 01:06:57,076
Ms. Dam. There's something
I need to tell you.

895
01:07:06,043 --> 01:07:08,045
Subtitle translation by Juyoung Park
